<ZenmerchDocsLayout
  title="ZenMerch Theme Integration (OS 2.0)"
  description="Enable the ZenMerch app embed and add the theme app block to your product template (Online Store 2.0)."
>
  <article class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h1>Theme integration (Online Store 2.0)</h1>
    <p>
      ZenMerch integrates using Shopify’s supported extension architecture: a <strong>theme app block</strong> for the personalizer UI and an
      <strong> app embed</strong> for global behavior (when needed). This avoids risky manual theme code edits.
    </p>

    <h2 id="embed">Enable the app embed</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>In ZenMerch, go to <strong>Settings → Theme integration</strong>.</li>
      <li>Click <strong>Enable ZenMerch embed</strong> to open Shopify Theme Editor.</li>
      <li>In Theme Editor → <strong>App embeds</strong>, enable the ZenMerch embed, then <strong>Save</strong>.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="block">Add the personalizer block</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>In ZenMerch, click <strong>Add personalizer block</strong> (opens Theme Editor on a product template).</li>
      <li>Add the ZenMerch app block inside <strong>Product information</strong>.</li>
      <li>
        Placement recommendation: put it <strong>above the buy buttons</strong> for best conversion and usability.
      </li>
      <li>Click <strong>Save</strong> in Theme Editor.</li>
    </ol>

    <ScreenshotFigure
      src="/images/zenmerch/screenshots/Admin-Settings-ThemeIntegration.png"
      alt="ZenMerch admin theme integration settings"
      caption="Theme integration: enable the app embed, then add the product page block in Theme Editor."
      aspectClass="aspect-[16/9]"
    />

    <h2 id="verify">Verify it’s working</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Open any targeted product page.</li>
      <li>Confirm the ZenMerch UI appears on the product page.</li>
      <li>Interact with inputs and confirm the preview updates.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="status">Diagnostics</h2>
    <p>
      If you make changes in Theme Editor, use <strong>Refresh status</strong> inside ZenMerch to rescan the embed/block status.
    </p>
  </article>
</ZenmerchDocsLayout>

